Table 2. Summary for subfitness

For Dedekind-MacNeille completions that are distributive, the notion of $\mathcal{D} \mathcal{M}$-regular is simply $\mathcal{B} \mathcal{L}$-regular plus subfit (Proposition 5.7). Also, the notions of $\mathcal{J}$ - and $(\cdot)^{\sigma}$-regular coincide with being Boolean (Propositions 5.21 and 5.22).

![table_2](table_2)

Table 3. Summary for regularity
For $\mathrm{A} \in$ DLat, consider the following definitions relating to Booleanness:

- A is $\mathcal{D} \mathcal{M}$-Boolean if $\mathcal{D} M A$ is Boolean;
- A is $\mathcal{B} \mathcal{L}$-Boolean if $\mathcal{B} \mathcal{L} A$ is Boolean (equivalently, $p \mathcal{J}(A$ is Boolean);
- A is $\mathcal{J}$-Boolean if $\mathcal{J} A$ is Boolean;

The notion of $(\cdot)^{\sigma}$-Boolean is simply Boolean (Proposition 6.6).

